briefdescription.para: Computes checksums on Eeprom or Memory types.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Computes checksums up to MaxBytesPerCycle bytes every call. This function is used to compute checksums for Eeprom, Memory, the OS code segment and the cFE core code segment

parameterdescription.para: A pointer to the entry in a table that we want to compute the checksum on.
A pointer to the computed checksum that will be assigned the checksum of the entry.
A pointer to a boolean that will be assigned a value based on whether or not the specified entry's checksum was completed.
Value used to determine the computed checksum, if completed
Value that specifies whether or not the specified entry's checksum was completed during this call.

entry.para: Success return code when a checksum compare did not fail.
Error code returned when a checksum compare failed.

briefdescription.para: Child task main function for recomputing baselines for Eeprom and Memory types.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Child task main function that is spawned when a recompute baseline command is received for Eeprom, Memory, OS code segment or cFE core code segment.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: Only one child task for CS can be running at any one time.
